<HEADLINE> US Raider Val's Prince Wins Horse Racing Cup in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 14 (Xinhua) -- American raider Val's Prince
and its international rider Cash Asmussen came from behind in a
late run to win the Hong Kong International Cup here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Val's Prince, winner of the group one turf classic invitational
 stakes at Belmont Park in October, edged locally trained Oriental
 Express by a short head. The two finished the 1,800-meter race
in identical times of one minute 47.20 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Representing Britain, Wixim ridden by Michael Kinane from
Britain came third.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, awarded the trophy to Asmussen after his
victory.
</P>
<P>
Luso, representing Britain, also ridden by Kinane, won the
International Vase over 2,400 meters while the International Bowel
 title over a course of 1,400 meters was taken by Catalan Opening,
 which represented Australia, and its Australian rider Darren
Beadman.
</P>
<P>
The international, fourth in the annual series, was the first
international horse race held here by the Hong Kong Jockey Club
after Hong Kong's return to China on July 1.  
</P>
</TEXT>
