<HEADLINE> Asian Games Flame Settled At New Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 14 (Xinhua) -- New Delhi's National
Stadium, venue of the inaugural Asian Games in 1951, on Sunday
became the permanent home for the Asian Games flame.
</P>
<P>
Olympic Council of Asia (OCA) president Sheikh Ahmed Al-Fahad
Al-Sabah of Kuwait lit the flame which will be relayed from the
National Stadium to the cities hosting all future summer and
winter Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
The OCA president said:"To have history one needs roots and our
roots are here, it was here that the Asian Games movement was
born."
</P>
<P>
The Asian Games have developed to the second-largest gathering
of athletes in the world after the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
OCA general secretary Randhir Singh said that torch relays
from New Delhi to cities hosting the Asian Games would become a
regular feature of the continent's sporting scene every two years.
</P>
<P>
"Similar to the traditional lighting of the Olympic Games
torch, the Asian Games torch in future editions will be lit from
the flame at the National Stadium," said Singh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
