<HEADLINE> Georgian President Leaves for Visit to Bulgaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Georgian President Eduard
Shevardnadze left the capital of Tbilisi for a visit to Sofia,
Bulgaria Sunday.
</P>
<P>
His visit is aimed at promoting a global project of
establishing a Eurasian transport corridor, said a report of the
Interfax news agency from Tbilisi. Shevardnadze had visited
several other countries involved in the project.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, seven interstate agreements, including a
joint declaration by presidents of the two countries, and a
consular convention are expected to be signed, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents will discuss the development of the
transport communications, including a ferry line between the
Bulgarian port of Varna and the Georgian port of Poti, and also
economic cooperation between the two countries, said Georgian
presidential spokesman Vakhtang Abashidze. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
