<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Host Integrated Development Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 14 (Xinhua) -- A two-day regional conference
opened in Chinhoyi of north Zimbabwe today with the aim of
stimulating integrated development in southern Africa.
</P>
<P>
Organizer of the conference, Zimbabwe Integrated Program (ZIP)
today said the conference is part of a larger project to promote
integrated development in the region using its experience in
Zimbabwe to generate similar activities in other countries.
</P>
<P>
ZIP said in a statement that two special characteristics of
its program, the promotion of linkages between developmental
activities and networking between professionals and grass-roots
will be presented as role models to other southern African
countries.
</P>
<P>
The speakers at the conference from Zambia, Tanzania,
Botswana, Zimbabwe, Malawi and the Democratic Republic of Congo
(DRC) will present papers on recent socio-economic development in
the Southern African Development Community (SADC).
</P>
<P>
The papers also dwell on democratic changes in central Africa
including trends and challenges for political and economic
development, the role of the media in integrated development and
the impact of economic reforms in the countries of the region.
</P>
</TEXT>
