<HEADLINE> World War II Bomb Defused After Mass Evacuation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 14 (Xinhua) -- About 26,000 residents were
evacuated out of the western German city of Ludwigshafen today as
bomb experts moved in to defuse a 4,000-pound bomb dating back to
the World War II.
</P>
<P>
Several hours after the mass evacuations, experts announced
that the bomb, which was found Friday in a field next to a
highway, had been successfully defused.
</P>
<P>
In case of an explosion, residential buildings within a radius
of 70 meters would be totally destroyed, experts said, adding that
the huge impact would also damage an alkohol factory some 200
meters away from the bomb site.
</P>
<P>
Nearby railway, river and air transportation services have also
been interrupted for several hours during the operations which
involved over 1,200 local officials and aid workers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
