<DOCNO> XIE19971215.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain Warns EU against Beef Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Britain will block beef imports
from other European Union countries if they do not comply with the
standards set out by an agreed plan to improve butchery practices
and make it safer to eat, agriculture minister Jack Cunningham
said today.
</P>
<P>
He told BBC television that EU farm ministers agreed in July to
adopt a new hygiene policy from the start of next year under which
the brains, eyes and spinal columns of cattle would be removed
after slaughter.
</P>
<P>
"There are now signs in Brussels that the opponents of that
decision have been working to have the implementation date put
back again," Cunningham said.
</P>
<P>
If fellow EU farm ministers drag their heels over the plan at a
meeting this week, Cunningham warned, he will ask parliament for
powers to bar imports of carcasses from which high-risk offal has
not been removed.
</P>
<P>
The EU has banned exports of British beef since March last year
following a discovery by scientists that mad cow disease could be
transmitted to humans who ate infected meat.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
