<DOCNO> XIE19971215.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yemeni President Visits Oman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni President Ali
Abdullah Saleh arrived in Oman's capital Muscat today for a
three-day official visit, the Omani News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival, Saleh told reporters that he will discuss
with Omani leaders ways and means of promoting bilateral
cooperation, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Observers noted that Saleh's visit came before the forthcoming
summit of the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) due on December 20-22
in Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
He is believed to seek Oman's support for Yemen's application
for GCC membership.
</P>
<P>
Yemen submitted its application last year to the regional
economic, political and defense alliance, which groups Oman,
Kuwait, Saudi Arabia, Qatar, Bahrain and the United Arab Emirates.
</P>
<P>
Yemen's ties with GCC members soured in 1990 due to its support
for Iraq in the Gulf crisis. It has been trying to mend fences
with the oil-rich countries after the 1991 Gulf War, which drove
Iraq out of Kuwait. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
