<HEADLINE> Russian Premier to Visit Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Russian Premier Viktor
Chernomyrdin said here today that Russia welcomed the reports that
Turkey is ready to change the rules of navigation in the Black sea
straits.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin made the remark prior to his visit to Turkey. He
said Russia has always opposed the unilateral adoption by Turkey
of the navigation regulations in the Black Sea straits, as some of
its provisions are against the principles of free navigation
stipulated in the international convention signed in Montreal in
1936, according to the Interfax.
</P>
<P>
However, the Russian premier said, Russia is ready to cooperate
with Turkey in this area on the condition that the convention and
the recommendations by the international Maritime Organization are
observed.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that "practical problems of navigation in the
Black Sea straits can be tackled without amending this document,
given good will and readiness to cooperate on the basis of
international law."
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin said that Russia is determined to broaden the
bilateral cooperation with Turkey in the area of power. He
expressed hope that his coming visit to Turkey would promote the
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The volume of trade of the two countries has reached four
billion U.S. Dollars, up 17 percent compared with last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
