<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Meets With Ramos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin met with Philippine President Fidel Ramos here tonight and
the two leaders expressed happiness at seeing each other again
after a meeting not long ago, believing such frequent meetings are
conducive to the development of relations between their two
countries.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Jiang said that over the past year, the
overall relationship between the two nations has maintained its
momentum of development, to which the Philippine president has
contributed a lot.
</P>
<P>
"We would continue to work for safeguarding and developing the
friendly relationship and long-standing and smooth cooperation
between China and the Philippines," Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
While agreeing to Jiang's view, Ramos said the two countries
have also made new headway in cooperation in the space and
maritime fields.
</P>
<P>
He also hoped that trade between the two nations would be
further expanded and China's investment in the Philippines
increased.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said the Philippines and China have also had peaceful
consultations on the South China Sea issue, which are helpful to
maintaining regional peace and stability and to furthering the two
countries' relations as well.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine president said his country would continue to
address the disputes between the two sides through peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang, while expressing his agreement with Ramos,
noted that both China and the Philippines are working for economic
development, which calls for a stable environment.
</P>
<P>
"We can shelve our disputes and increase our joint studies and
cooperation," Jiang stressed.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also believed that the informal summit of East
Asian nations held here earlier today is the first of its kind in
history.
</P>
<P>
It is very important that the leaders of ASEAN, China, Japan
and South Korea sit together and seek to boost cooperation between
them, Jiang said, stressing that "it is imperative for us to
explore ways of addressing the current financial turmoil."
</P>
<P>
Both presidents are here to attend informal summits between
ASEAN and China, Japan and South Korea and between ASEAN and
China.  
