<HEADLINE> Northeast China City to Build New Wild Animal Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Officials in Shenyang,
capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province, plan to rebuild
its wild animal park to better protect its inhabitants.
</P>
<P>
The new park is expected to cover an area of 3.3 million square
meters, and will have at least 200 species representing the
animals of northeast China.
</P>
<P>
About 10,000 animals will be in the new park. The park, unlike
the zoo, is a nature reserve where animals roam free so that they
can "return to the wild."
</P>
<P>
The present wild animal park, located in the southeast area of
the city, occupies only an area of 460,000 square meters and has
only 100 species of animals, which are mainly fed by the keepers.
</P>
<P>
According to official sources, experts are investigating the
terrain, hydrology and vegetation of sites in the southeast and
northeast of Shenyang to choose the best location. 
