<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 14:30 GMT, December 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- The second round of official talks on Iraq's
dismarment between Iraq and the United Nations Special Commission
(UNSCOM) started here Monday morning, Iraqi News Agency (INA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tariq Aziz represented the Iraqi
side while Richard Butler, executive director of the UNSCOM on
dismantling Iraq's weapons of mass destruction, headed the U.N.
side, according to the INA.
</P>
<P>
Political observers here believe the second round of the talks
focus on the delicate question of the entry of the U.N. arms
inspectors into the Iraqi presidential palaces which Iraq
considers as symbols of its sovereignty. (Iraq-UNSCOM-Talks)
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- Louise Arbour, the general prosecutor for the Hague
International Tribunal hearing war crimes in ex-Yugoslavia, Monday
criticized France for not cooperating with the tribunal in
providing evidence.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the daily, Liberation, Arbour said France
bans its military officers who served in peace-keeping forces in
ex-Yugoslavia from testifying before the court in person.
</P>
<P>
The Serb war criminals "feel absolutely safe" in the zone
controlled by French troops serving in the multi-national
stabilization force (SFOR) in Bosnia, she said.
(France-International Tribunal)
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- The Indonesian rupiah continued to weaken today
against the U.S. dollar as people here still worried about the
health of President Soeharto.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah was quoted at 5,490 against the dollar in the
morning before it recovered to 5,350 per dollar at 10:00 a.m. The
rupiah closed at 5,150/5,250 against the dollar last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Currency dealers said people here still worried about the
health of President Soeharto after the announcement that he could
not attend an informal ASEAN summit in Malaysia.
(Indonesia-Rupiah-Drop)
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Secretary General of Iran's Freedom Movement Ebrahim
Yazdi was arrested Sunday, a statement from the organization
announced today.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that Yazdi was summoned by the Islamic
Revolutionary Court Sunday for investigations and was put into
Tehran's famous prison of Evin Sunday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
It said that so far no official charges were announced against
Yazdi, former Iranian foreign minister of the interim government
led by late former Prime Minister Mehdi Bazargan after the Islamic
Revolution in 1979. (Iran-Yazdi-Arrest) 
</P>
