<HEADLINE> British Warship Calls at Hong Kong Harbor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The British Navy destroyer,
HMS Norttigham, came here today for a four-day stop, thus becoming
the first British warship to berth in the SAR since the July 1
handover.
</P>
<P>
The HMS Nottingham, one of 12 Type-42 destroyers in service
with the British Royal Navy, is moored in the harbor at a buoy off the
Extension to the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center "for
rest and recreation."
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the British Consulate-General in Hong Kong
confirmed that the 12 destroyers form the backbone of the Royal
Navy's anti-air warfare force.
</P>
<P>
The HMS Nottingham, with a length of 125 meters, displacement
of 4,100 tons and 250 officers and sailors on board, has been in
service for 14 years.  
</P>
