<HEADLINE> Israel Seals and Demolishes Suicide Bombers' Homes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Israeli security forces
today sealed and demolished homes of families of suicide bombers
who carried out attacks in Jerusalem this summer, Israel Radio
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said that two houses were destroyed and another two
were sealed off in the Palestinian village of Aseera Al-Shamaliya
near the West Bank city of Nablus.
</P>
<P>
Israeli security forces got permission from Israeli High Court
last week to take the demolition actions in a bid to "curb
terrorism."
</P>
<P>
The court said that the families provided food and shelter to
terrorists for a long period of time; and court President Aharon
Barak stressed that the intent of the punishment is to deter
potential terrorists in the future.
</P>
<P>
Five Hamas activists blew off themselves in Jerusalem's Mahaneh
Yehuda Market and Ben Yehuda Shopping Mall this summer, killing
25 people and wounding hundreds. Since the attacks, Israeli
security forces have been beefed up in the territories to fight
terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Palestinian and Israeli human rights groups said
hundreds of homes in areas of the West Bank which remain under
Israeli military control have been threatened with demolition.
</P>
</TEXT>
