ruling party's presidential candidate in the 1998 polls, instead
of de Villa as had been speculated.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held today, de Villa announced his
breakaway from the ruling party and his decision to run for the
presidency next year despite the fact that he does not have the
endorsement of President Ramos.
</P>
<P>
"Lakas-NUCD-UMDP remains the biggest party in the Philippines
and the party of the future," de Venecia added in the statement.
