<HEADLINE> Shanghai Airport Reports Decade-Long Flight Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Hongqiao International
Airport of Shanghai Sunday marked 10 consecutive years of flight
safety.
</P>
<P>
Forty-two overseas and domestic airlines are operating out of
Hongqiao on more than 300 air routes. A decade ago, only 20 air
carriers were operating out of Hongqiao.
</P>
<P>
The airport handled 74.2 million travelers over the
decade. While bringing the on-time rate of flights to 99.99
percent, the airport increased its annual transport volume by more
than 15 percent.
</P>
<P>
While the airport has been expanding business, the emphasis
remained on safety. Statistics show that safety supervision
departments at Hongqiao Airport have seized 22,000 dangerous
articles and more than 2,100 forged travelling documents over the
10-year period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
