<HEADLINE> Russia Tries to Broaden Cooperation with EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Russia is actively trying to
broaden cooperation with the European Union (EU) and the
partership agreement between both sides is being implemented, a
Russian Foreign Ministry spokesman said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman, Valery Nesterushkin, said that the agreement
went into effect on December 1.
</P>
<P>
On the recent EU enlargement decision, the spokesman said that
Russia considers "this process to be objective as it reflects the
main tendency on the European continent".
</P>
<P>
Moscow holds that economic interdependence and cooperation will
constitute the nucleus of interstate relations in the 21st
century, Nesterushkin said.
</P>
<P>
On the Baltic countries' admission to the EU, he said, "their
involvement in the integration process will promote the solution
of hitherto unsolved humanitarian problems, first of all the
situation of ethnic Russians in those countries."
</P>
<P>
The EU summit, which ended in Luxembourg Saturday, decided to
start the process of admitting 10 central and eastern European
countries as well as Cyprus to the union.
</P>
<P>
Among the candidates for admission are Estonia, Latvia and
Lithuania, the former Soviet republics. 
</P>
