<HEADLINE> Small, Medium-sized Enterprises Center Set Up in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Small and medium-sized
enterprises (SMEs), which form the backbone of the Hong Kong
economy, will be able to get an easy access to a variety of
services starting today with the launch of the SME Center.
</P>
<P>
The SME Center, acting as a "total solutions" service provider,
is set up by Hong Kong Productivity Council (HKPC), with funding
from the Special Administrative Region (SAR) government.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony, Kenneth Fang, chairman of
HKPC, said, the performance of SMEs, which account for 98 percent
of Hong Kong's business establishments, is critically important to
the prosperity of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
With rising costs in Hong Kong, industry and businesses must
develop in the direction of high value-added productivity, Fang
said.
</P>
<P>
"Strengthening research and development capabilities and
improving management quality are important means toward this goal.
However, efforts in these areas involve significant financial and
manpower investment. SMEs, because of their size and limited
resources, must therefore rely on external support to improve
their competitiveness," he said.
</P>
<P>
Also officiating at the ceremony was Denise Yue, secretary for
trade and industry of the SAR, who pointed out that SMEs are now
faced with ever keener competition.
</P>
<P>
"With the opening of the center, SMEs will be able to meet the
challenges they encounter in the course of their business and
enhance their competitiveness in the global market," she said.
</P>
<P>
Located on the fourth floor of the HKPC building, the SME
Center is a one-stop service center that aims at providing SMEs
with easy access to a network of service providers covering areas
of banking and finance, information technology, forwarding and
shipping, telecommunications and insurance, among others.
</P>
<P>
The HKPC was established by statute in 1967 with the aim to
promote productivity excellence through the provision of
professional services.  
</P>
</TEXT>
