<HEADLINE> Portuguese Language School Designated in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 15 (Xinhua) -- A Macao school has been
designated as the future Portuguese language school after the
establishment of the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) in
December 1999.
</P>
<P>
Portuguese Education Minister Eduardo Marcal Grilo and
representatives of the local Oriental Foundation and a local
society signed an agreement last Saturday, designating the
Commerce School as the Portuguese language school after 1999.
</P>
<P>
According to a report in today's Va Kio newspaper, the
Portuguese Ministry of Education and the Oriental Foundation will
jointly fund the operation of the Portuguese language school.
</P>
<P>
The Basic Law of Macao stipulates that in addition to the
Chinese language, Portuguese may also be used as an official
language by the executive authorities, legislature and judiciary
of the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Han Zhaokang, chief representative of the Chinese
side of the Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group, told the
newspaper that in establishing such a school, government assets,
if any, must be maintained and the rights and authority of the
future SAR government respected.
</P>
<P>
Han said the Chinese side has agreed in principle to the
establishment of a Portuguese language school and further
technical negotiations are under way.  
</P>
</TEXT>
