<HEADLINE> Macao Casino Business Rises 10 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Business in Macao casinos has
increased by about 10 percent so far this year, casino magnate
Stanley Ho said.
</P>
<P>
Today's Macao Daily News quoted Ho, general manager of the
Macao Tourism and Amusement Company, which monopolizes casinos in
Macao, as saying he was "satisfied with the performance of the
gambling business."
</P>
<P>
The report did not say how much his company has earned so far
this year.
</P>
<P>
The casino business suffered a blow earlier this year as triad
fighting for casino-related profits escalated. However, the
situation has been improved in the latter half of the year.
</P>
<P>
Macao casinos hand over 31.8 percent of their gross profits to
the government as tax, which accounts for about 40 percent of
Macao's revenue income.  
</P>
