and his government have made to promote the state's ties with
China, saying that bilateral cooperation will be strengthened in
various sectors.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of Premier Kennett, Victorian Minister for Education
Phil Gude and Melbourne Mayor Ivan Deveson extended their welcome
to Li. They expressed the belief that Li's visit will push forward
the ties between Australia and China, as well as those between
Victoria and China's provinces and cities.
</P>
<P>
In the evening, Victorian Governor James Gobbo hosted a banquet
in honor of the Chinese guest.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Li toured the Broken Hill Proprietary Co. Ltd.,
the largest company of Australia, which has maintained trading
ties with China for a century.  
