<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Further Weakens Against Greenback </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian rupiah
continued to weaken today against the U.S. dollar as people here
still worried about the health of President Soeharto.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah was quoted at 5,490 against the dollar in the
morning before it recovered to 5,350 per dollar at 10:00 a.m. The
rupiah closed at 5,150/5,250 against the dollar last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Currency dealers said people here still worried about the
health of President Soeharto after the announcement that he could
not attend an informal ASEAN summit in Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Minister/State Secretary Moerdiono said last Friday that
President Soeharto decided to cancel his trip to Kuala Lumpur as
doctors advised him to take a full 10-day rest.
</P>
<P>
Another reason for the drop of the rupiah is the weakness of
regional currencies such as those of the Philippines, Thailand,
Malaysia and Singapore. Reports said the Philippine peso and the
Thai baht reached record lows today against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian rupiah has suffered the most so far this year,
having dropped by 117 percent against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Share prices on the Jakarta Stock Exchange plunged
3.9 percent, with the composite index down 14.272 points to reach
351.579.
</P>
</TEXT>
