<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Weaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar tumbled
below 66.00 U.S. cents today on ongoing pessimism about Asian
economies, and traders said the local currency was likely to
capitulate to further selling pressure over coming days.
</P>
<P>
The local unit finished almost half a U.S. cent lower at 65.88
US cents from 66.32 U.S. cents late Friday, after dipping to a new
four-year low of 65.80 intraday.
</P>
<P>
Traders said the slide was exacerbated by the release of the
latest Japanese Tankan report which painted a pessimistic outlook
for that country's economy.
</P>
<P>
The report confirmed the view that the Japanese economy,
already in a slowdown three months ago, was battered even more by
the recent major financial failures in Japan and the Asian
financial and economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
An expert said the region's financial woes continued to keep
pressure on the Australian dollar, ruling out any rebound.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar ended in Sydney at 86.56 yen, from 86.21
previously and at 1.1722 marks, from 1.1696.  
</P>
</TEXT>
