<HEADLINE> Ganz Set to Leave Inter Milan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Bitter striker Maurizio Ganz is
set to leave the talent-packed Inter Milan in the New Year, he
told a local newspapers on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"By now, it's clear that with Ronaldo and (Youri) Djorkaeff
there's no place here for me," the 29-year-old striker told
Gazzetta dello Sport.
</P>
<P>
Ganz was seeking in the new season for a starting place in
Inter's front since the arrival of Brazilian Ronaldo, who not only
strengthenes Inter's attacking power, but also brings intense
competition for place in the fixed striking pair.
</P>
<P>
"I just want a team in which to play for a place Sunday after
Sunday. Here the front-line is fixed," Ganz added.
</P>
<P>
AC Milan is the first choice for Ganz, who scored 10 goals in
last year's UEFA Cup final for Inter, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Milan's manager Fabio Capello has asked Inter for Ganz,
according to one report.
</P>
<P>
Inter president Massimo Moratti, however, is unlikely release
the player until January's Intalian Cup quarter-final clash
between the arch-rivals. 
</P>
