<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Expected to Reach Macro-Economic Control Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) -- China is expected to reach its
macro-control target this year to achieve a steady growth in the
national economy, a statistics official has said.
</P>
<P>
judging from the major economic indices for the present, Ye
Zhen, spokesman for the State Statistics Bureau (SSB), said in an
interview with Xinhua, "In spite of the problems like inefficiency
and irrational economic structure, the Chinese economy will
maintain a rapid but appropriate growth this year as was showed in
the past eleven months."
</P>
<P>
He pointed to the bumper harvest in agriculture, steadily
growing industry, appropriate growth in the investment returns,
consumption, and export sector, effectively reined inflation, and
continual rise in urban residents' income.
</P>
<P>
The SSB spokesman said the national economy this year mainly
features a rapid but appropriate growth, with the gross domestic
product (GDP) increasing by nine percent on an annual basis during
the January-October period.
</P>
<P>
The national economy has actually achieved high growth in
tandem with low inflation, since the market prices have stablized
generally for the present, and the social consumer price index
only edged up 1.1 percent on an annual basis during the
January-October period and even dropped in October, according to
Ye.
</P>
<P>
What is noteworthy is that the Chinese industrial sector
reported increasing economic efficiency this year, with the
combined profits from the industrial ventures above the township
level rising 25.2 percent during the first ten months this year.
</P>
<P>
Another salient feature of the Chinese economy during the
period lies in a rational growth in fixed asset investment and
improved investment destination, Ye Zhen pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The fixed asset investment increased by 12.1 percent on a
yearly basis, with the input into the primary sector rising 60.9
percent over the same period last year, accounting for 2.5 percent
of the total amount, compared with the 1.8 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
The basic industries like the transportation, post and
telecommunications also received 11.5 percent more of funds than
last year, while the investment in western areas saw accelerated
growth of 21.9 percent, much higher than in eastern and central
areas.
</P>
<P>
Foreign trade continued to increase during the period, with the
export business forging ahead. By the end of November, the foreign
trade surplus had exceeded 35.6 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Against the backdrop of spreading financial volatility in
southeast Asian countries, China accumulated 135 billion US
dollars in foreign exchange reserve and used a total of 44 billion
US dollars of foreign investment during the first three quarters
this year, up 23.8 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
"Judging from the numerous macro-economic indices for the
present, we can say that China has basically achieved the target
set for this year and the Chinese economy as a whole has become
better than in any of the past several years," the SSB spokesman
stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
