<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Freedom Movement Chief Arrested in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General of Iran's
Freedom Movement Ebrahim Yazdi was arrested Sunday, a statement
from the organization announced today.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that Yazdi was summoned by the Islamic
Revolutionary Court Sunday for investigations and was put into
Tehran's famous prison of Evin Sunday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
It said that so far no official charges were announced
against Yazdi, former Iranian foreign minister of the interim
government led by late former Prime Minister Mehdi Bazargan
after the Islamic Revolution in 1979.
</P>
<P>
An Iranian informed source told Xinhua through a telephone
call that Yazdi was arrested possibly on a charge of having
"illegal political activities" in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Freedom Movement was founded in 1961 by Bazargan and
fought against the former Iranian Shah regime. It joined the
first government after the Islamic Revolution but withdrew from
it due to some differences with the late Iranian Supreme
Leader Ruhollah Mosavi Khomeini.
</P>
<P>
Ebrahim Yazdi was elected as secretary general of the party
in January 1985 after Bazargan's demise. However, the party was
not granted formal permission to have activities since the
country announced to register political parties and organizations
in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Yazdi announced his readiness to participate the May
presidential elections, but his candidacy was rejected by the
Iranian authorities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
