<HEADLINE> Jiang Upbeat About East Asian Economies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin said here Monday that the prospect for East Asia's economic
development is promising.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said this while addressing the Informal Summit Meeting of
East Asian Heads of State or Government.
</P>
<P>
He said:"Looking into the 21st century, we can say with full
confidence that relatively sound conditions are available for East
Asia to raise its economic and social development to a new level."
</P>
<P>
Over the past two or three decades, economic growth in this
region ranks the highest among the world and people's standard of
living has also improved rapidly, he added.
</P>
<P>
He cited three reasons as support for his remark.
</P>
<P>
Firstly, it is the shared desire of these countries to develop
economy.
</P>
<P>
Secondly, they have built up certain economic strength. Some
countries have entered the developed stage, others have joined the
rank of newly industrialized nations, and still others have
embarked on the road of rapid growth.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Jiang said, these countries have created their own
fine cultural traditions and the development of economic
cooperation in the region will be further boosted with a spiritual
motive force.
</P>
<P>
With all this, the regional economies can provide useful
experience and set a model for economic cooperation among
countries and regions in the world, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
