<DOCNO> XIE19971215.0131 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Financial Cooperation in East Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin Monday urged East Asian countries to strengthen
international and regional financial cooperation in a bid to
maintain international financial order.
</P>
<P>
In his speech to the Informal Summit Meeting of East Asian
Heads of State or Government here, Jiang said it is imperative for
East Asian countries to improve their financial system, policy and
supervision and jointly ward off excessive speculation by
international hot money which caused the recent financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
He said East Asia should look squarely into the current
difficulties and obstacles in their economies such as irrational
economic structure, imperfect financial system, extensive mode of
growth, backward infrastructures and overpopulation, which need to
be addressed carefully and in real earnest.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, he is confident East Asia would overcome the
economic difficulties brought about by the financial turmoil with
the good economic fundamentals and other favorable factors enjoyed
by East Asia.
</P>
<P>
China has taken a positive approach toward strengthening
financial cooperation in East Asia and is ready to take part in
relevant discussion, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
China would perfect its all-dimensional, multi-tiered and wide
ranging opening-up pattern, foster an open economy and actively
participate in regional economic cooperation and global
multilateral trading system.
</P>
<P>
Jiang says China's economic development would provide greater
opportunities for trade, investment and cooperation in this region
and an access to a huge market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
