<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen on China-ASEAN Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen today expressed his satisfaction over
the relations between China and ASEAN nations and between China
and ASEAN as an organization, saying the relations have made
significant progress in the last decade.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech at a business forum titled "A Private
Sector Salute to ASEAN" here this afternoon, Qian mentioned that
since China became a full dialogue partner of ASEAN last year,
"China-ASEAN relations have reached a new level".
</P>
<P>
He said, "Through frequent political exchanges, steadily
expanding economic cooperation and trade and candid dialogue and
consultations, we have enhanced mutual understanding, deepened
trust, broadened common ground and increased friendship."
</P>
<P>
Facts have shown that China and ASEAN are important forces for
peace and development, stability and cooperation, he said, adding
that maintaining friendly relations and cooperation between China
and ASEAN serves the interests of both sides and also brings
benefits to the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Qian also spoke highly of ASEAN's positive role in keeping with
its unique approach in safeguarding peace, promoting development
and strengthening cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said, "We have noted with pleasure that over the past three
decades, especially since the beginning of the 1990s, ASEAN
countries have worked unremittingly for national and regional
resilience and achieved remarkable success."
</P>
<P>
In the course of its development, ASEAN has initiated the
famous ASEAN Way, which highlights non-interference in the
internal affairs of countries, respects diversity, stresses equal
participation, pursues consensus through consultations, cherishes
mutually beneficial cooperation and stands for incremental
progress, he said.
</P>
<P>
Following this approach, ASEAN has withstood numerous tests, he
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
