<HEADLINE> International Business of ICBC Shanghai Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Since it accepted the first
deposit in foreign currency in 1987, the Shanghai Branch of the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC) has managed to
expand its foreign exchange assets to 3.42 billion US dollars by
the June this year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, its foreign currency deposits hit 1.34 billion US
dollars by June, with the outstanding loans in foreign currency
reaching 740 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
During the past ten years, the bank conducted international
settlements worth 13.36 billion US dollars, buying and selling 6.02
billion US dollars in foreign exchanges, realizing 177 million US
dollars in profit.
</P>
<P>
The expansion provided firm backing for the local large
state-owned enterprises to import equipment, upgrade technology,
enter for international bidding, and tap overseas market, said an
ICBC official.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai branches of world-famous multinationals also
benefited from the bank's international service, while the
municipality received syndicated loans from the bank to expedite
the construction of city infrastructure and development of Pudong
New Area, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
For the present, the bank has its own foreign exchange service
network in Shanghai, comprising more than 60 service outlets.
</P>
<P>
The bank also becomes the agent bank of more than 350 overseas
banks, and has business relations with more than 3,000 overseas
financial institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
