<HEADLINE>   Foreign Illegal Immigrants Forced to Leave Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 15 (Xinhua) -- About 5,000 foreign
illegal immigrants have left Kuwait and 10,000 regularized their
residence status during a two-and-half-month grace period ending
today, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait Interior Ministry started the amnesty period at the
beginning of October, demanding the illegals to leave the country
within the period without paying fines.
</P>
<P>
During the period, Kuwait Interior Ministry increased
inspections in areas where they suspected that illegal foreign
residents were staying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Ministry of Social Affairs and Labor has
been checking on the residence status of students in various
private schools.
</P>
<P>
Students of private schools were given until December 13
this month to show a copy of their valid civil identity
cards to their schools, or they would be suspended.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait's campaign to clean illegal foreign residents was within
the framework of a common effort in the Gulf Arab countries to
clear illegal expatriates. Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates
and Oman also carried out similar campaigns earlier this year
during which deferent amnesty period were granted to illegal
aliens to leave without punishment.
</P>
<P>
About 1.3 million foreign laborers and their families are
living in Kuwait, accounting for 65 percent of its 2 million
population. Illegal foreign laborers are marginal comparing with
that in other Gulf countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
