<HEADLINE> Guangzhou's Foreign Trade Up 10 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, registered a foreign trade volume of
6.1 billion US dollars in the first ten months this year.
</P>
<P>
With a year-on-year growth of more than 10 percent, the city
ranked among China's top ten biggest cities.
</P>
<P>
Exports of overseas-funded ventures in the city contributed 60
percent of the total, up ten percentage points than that for the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Processing industry registered a fast growth with the export
volume up 27 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to local traders, local clothes and other fabrics
become more competitive in the international market. Other exports
include electronic products and arts and crafts.
</P>
<P>
Its exports to Europe, Middle East, Africa and Latin America
have increased, apart from its traditional importers of Hong Kong,
the United States and Japan. Its exports to Europe and Africa grew
more than 50 percent.  
</P>
