ROME -- The death of Giovanni Alberto Agnelli, the acknowledged
heir to the Fiat auto empire, will not change the accepted
scenario for the group's leadership in the near future, Fiat
Honorary Chairman Gianni Agnelli said today.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Fiat-owned daily La Stampa, he said
his nephew Alberto Agnelli was never in line to take over at the
company helm when current Chairman Cesare Romiti retires in 1998
or 1999. (Italy-Fiat-Leadership)
</P>
<P>
