<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Township enterprises will
become a development focus for the rural economy in the Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region, according to Wang Fengqi,
vice-chairman of the regional government.
</P>
<P>
The region's township enterprises have maintained strong growth
in recent years, with their production value totaling 122.8
billion yuan (14.8 billion U.S. dollars) last year, compared with
68 billion yuan (8.2 billion U.S. dollars) in 1995.
