<HEADLINE> China's Chemical Industry Develops New Blueprint </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Chemical
Industry has recently released industry objectives to the year
2010, today's Oversea's Edition of People's Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
The annual output value of the chemical industry will reach
1.67 trillion yuan in 2010 and have annual growth of 8.55 percent,
which quadruples the 1995 figure, according to the plan.
</P>
<P>
An increase in output of major products is expected, with
annual output of chemical fertilizer set at 38.2 million tons, and
a trillion tires expected to be produced in 2010.
</P>
<P>
By then, the quality of major products is expected to be at a
much higher level and energy consumption greatly reduced.
</P>
<P>
Production and environmental protection will be co-ordinated,
and growth momentum will be maintained, the plan says.  
