<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- India's annual rate of
inflation shot up by 0.61 percentage points to 3.96 percent for
the week ending November 29 mainly on account of an increase in
electricity tariffs, the local press said today.
</P>
<P>
The inflation was 6.67 percent during the corresponding week
last year.
</P>
<P>
