moment when the Claus-led cabinet was forced to resign on November
30 amid serious crises both within and outside the party.
</P>
<P>
The Civic Democratic Party was formed in April 1991 after its
separation from the former Civic Forum. It now has a total of
22,000 party members.
</P>
<P>
It won the right to form the cabinet following a victory in
general elections in parliament in June 1996. Klaus, in his
capacity as the party's president, was appointed prime minister
last July. 
