<P>
Prior to the 9 plus 3 summit which opens in Kuala Lumpur today,
President Jiang Zemin held talks with Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir and Vietnam Prime Minister Phan Van Khai yesterday.
</P>
<P>
-- The daily frontpaged a commentator's article today saying
that the success of restructuring the state-owned enterprises
relies on joint efforts from the government, society and the firms.
</P>
<P>
The commentary, titled "Success Relies on Joint Efforts," says
that some state-owned enterprises have suffered losses because of
their internal problems related to the managerial mechanism and
the external market environment.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), said
his Australian visit will help strengthen high-level exchanges,
enchance mutual understanding, expand shared beneficial
cooperation and promote joint development between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
In a speech at Melbourne International Airport soon after his
arrival yesterday, Li said the Chinese government consistently
views development of mutually beneficial cooperation with
Australia as important.
</P>
