<HEADLINE> Schools In Tibet Check Students' Eyesight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Eight schools in the Tibet
Autonomous Region recently checked the eyesight of 10,000 students
for government departments.
</P>
<P>
Starting next year, all students in the eight schools will have
their eyes checked annually in September and October, according to
an autonomous region education department official.
</P>
<P>
He said that the data will be used to determine the condition
of students' eyesight and a measurement of how to protect more
students from nearsightedness.
</P>
<P>
The official said that Tibet is one of the last three
provincial-level administrative regions in the country to monitor
eyesight. 
</P>
