<HEADLINE> Rusedski Named BBC Sports Personality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Greg Rusedski, the surprise
runner-up in this year's U.S. Open tennis tournament, was named
the BBC British Sports Personality of the Year on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski's British tennis rival Tim Henman was the runner-up
and multiple Olympic champion rower Steve Redgrave finished third
in the viewers' voting.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski, who was born in Montreal of Canada but has a British
passport, reached as high as No. 4 in this year's ATP Tour
rankings. 
