<HEADLINE> Tourist Site to be Listed on Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, December 15 (Xinhua) -- A share-holding company will
be formed and listed on a stock exchange to raise funds for
the development of the Huangguoshu Waterfall and other major
tourist attractions in Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
The Huangguoshu Travel Industry Co. Ltd., which is being
formed, will focus on the development of a 130-kilometer tourist
route linking Guiyang, the provincial capital, with Huangguoshu
Waterfall, China's largest, where four national scenic areas are
located.
</P>
<P>
With a unique landscape and colorful folklore, the route --
with the waterfall as the center -- is considered one of 12 newly
emerging tourist destinations in the country. However, since
Guizhou in southwest China is an underdeveloped mountainous
region, a lack of funds has hindered the route's development.
</P>
<P>
The new company plans to raise both domestic and overseas funds
for the construction and improvement of scenic spots for folklore
villages, river-rafting, hot-air ballooning and cliff
climbing. Improvements also are planned in transportation, hotels,
shopping, entertainment and sightseeing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
