<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Insurance Sector in Guangzhou Gaining Ground </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The insurance business in the
capital of Guangdong Province is making headway in spite of
increasing market competition.
</P>
<P>
The premium of Guangzhou already accounts for one-fourth
of the province's total with substantial progress also achieved in
standardizing the insurance market.
</P>
<P>
The city's insurance companies turned out a total revenue of
2.644 billion yuan during the January-September period, up 36.86
percent over the same period last year. The premium, on the other
hand, climbed more than 41 percent to 2.541 billion yuan during
that period.
</P>
<P>
The expansion of the insurance business is a result of the
increasing strength of the provincial economy, said Ma Jing, the
city's central bank governor.
</P>
<P>
With 18 percent of the nation's insurance income of 66 billion
yuan going to Guangdong Province last year, Guangzhou held more
than one-fourth of the province's total.
</P>
<P>
The city also became the second city after Shanghai to
experiment with opening up the insurance sector to overseas
businesses. So far, 18 overseas insurance companies have launched
representative offices in the city.
</P>
<P>
The city also made strides in standardizing and regulating the
youth market. A professional association was set up for more
self-discipline among the companies, and the city's central bank
also was tightened up supervision, to encourage fair competition
in the business.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
