<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eastern Province Leads China In Agricultural Machinery Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province, one
of the country's leading grain producers, now leads in the use of
farm machinery as well.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that machinery account for 59 percent of
Anhui's agricultural production. The province ranks first in the
country in the use of small tractors per unit of farmland also.
</P>
<P>
The Provincial Agricultural Machinery Bureau officials
attribute the high rate of machinery utilization to increasing
enthusiasm shown by local farmers, who have spent 4.2 billion yuan
for this purpose since last year.
</P>
<P>
The province can expect this year's agricultural machinery
business to be worth eight billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Machinery maintenance has had parallel development. The
province now has 50 county-level maintenance centers, 1,600
township service stations, and 16,000 machinery service teams in
villages. In addition, machine products are easily obtainable at
14,000 sales outlets throughout the province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
