<HEADLINE> Kimaiyo Keeps Honolulu Marathon Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Defeding champion Eric
Kimaiyo retained the Honolulu Marathon title, winning a close race
Sunday in a time of two hours, 12 minutes and 17 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old Kenyan set a new course record which was less
than a minute off the old race mark of 2:11:43 set in 1986 by his
compatriot Ibrahim Hussein.
</P>
<P>
Jimmy Muindi of Kenya was second, 13 seconds behind Kimaiyo.
Thabiso Moqhali of Lesotho was third, a second behind Muindi.
</P>
<P>
Svetlana Vasilieva of Russia won the woman's race, clocking
2:33:14, more than two minutes off the women's race record of
2:31:01 set by Carla Buerskins in 1986.
</P>
<P>
Irina Bogacheva of Kyrgyzstan placed second in 2:14:01.
</P>
</TEXT>
