<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Shipping Industry Booming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- China's shipping industry has
flourished since 1978, when the country launched its ongoing
reform and opening drive. The country's shipping sector now boasts
one of the largest fleets in the world.
</P>
<P>
These remarks by Vice-Minister of Communications Liu Songjin in
Shanghai were made recently at an international seminar on marine
technology.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that the Chinese government has attached
great importance to the development of the shipping industry and
has made it an important part of the country's transport
system. Great efforts have been made to build ports and water
ways, he added.
</P>
<P>
Major reform measures have been taken to reinvigorate the
shipping industry, including re-organizing many shipping companies
into three large groups -- China Ocean Shipping Group, China
Marine Shipping Group and the Yangtze River Shipping Group.
</P>
<P>
The three groups have 87.6 billion yuan in total assets and 28
million tons in handling capacity. Their capacity accounts for
56 percent of the country's entire shipping industry.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, China had 406 deep-water berths in its
coastal ports, and 110,000 kilometers of inland water channels and
514 berths.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this century, a number of trunk water channels
will be built along the Yangtze River, the Xijiang River, the
Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal, as well as the Yangtze River Delta
and the Zhujiang River Delta.
</P>
<P>
Currently, China has 360,000 civil vessels, with more than 310
international shipping companies, more than 1,300 coastal shipping
firms and more than 5,100 river shipping enterprises.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the country's total shipping volume reached 1.27
billion tons and 1,755 billion tons/kilometers. Meanwhile, Chinese
ports had started 120 regular international shipping routes,
operating 2,102 voyages every month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971215.0252 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
