<HEADLINE> German Man Arrested for Killing Two Danish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 14 (Xinhua) -- A 47-year-old German man has been
arrested for stabbing to death two Danes after a violent row at
the Women's World Handball Championship in Berlin on Saturday,
police said today.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the unemployed man from Berlin, who already
had a criminal record, had provoked an argument with the two
Danish fans and stabbed them down during the Danish team's
semi-final match with Russia on Saturday. All of them got drunk at
the moment.
</P>
<P>
Officials decided to step up security measures and ban alcohol
sales at the final match which was won by Denmark over Norway
today.
</P>
<P>
German politicians today also called for a general ban on
alcohol for all sports events. 
</P>
